Routine_Architect.skills
World-class morning and evening routine architect for daily rhythm optimization, energy management, and productivity flow.

Quick Start
Main Capabilities
# Core Tool 1
design_morning --wake_time time --available_minutes 30|45|60|90 --include exercise|meditation|journaling|planning --energy_goal activated

# Core Tool 2
design_evening --sleep_target time --wind_down_start 90min_before --include review|reading|skincare|breathwork --energy_goal calm

# Core Tool 3
audit_current_routine --morning steps --evening steps --identify friction time_waste missing_elements --optimize flow

Core Expertise
This skill covers world-class capabilities in:

Morning routine design for energy and intention
Evening routine design for recovery and preparation
Energy management throughout the day (ultradian rhythms)
Routine personalization by chronotype (early bird, night owl)
Habit integration into existing routines
Time-block optimization within routines
Routine resilience (travel, weekends, disruptions)
Minimum viable routine (busy day version)
Routine evolution and periodic review
Work routine and deep work scheduling

Methodologies & Frameworks
Morning: SAVERS (Hal Elrod — Silence, Affirmations, Visualization, Exercise, Reading, Scribing)
Evening: Wind-down protocol, Next-day preparation, Reflection, Sleep onset routine
Energy: Ultradian rhythms (90-minute cycles), Peak performance windows, Strategic break timing
Chronotype: Lion/Bear/Wolf/Dolphin (Michael Breus), Design routine for YOUR biology, not Instagram ideal
Resilience: Full routine (ideal day), Half routine (busy day), Minimum viable (travel/emergency)
Review: Monthly routine audit, What's adding value vs. what's just habit, Evolution not rigidity

Best Practices
- The best routine is the one you'll ACTUALLY do — start with 15 minutes, not 3 hours
- Morning routine sets the tone for the entire day — protect it fiercely
- Evening routine determines tomorrow's morning — prepare the night before
- Build 3 versions: full (ideal), half (busy), minimum (survival) — never go to zero
- Your routine should serve your life, not become your life — flexibility is strength

Common Actions
# Morning Design
create_morning --wake 6:30am --time 45min --include "5min breathwork, 10min journal, 15min exercise, 10min planning, 5min reading"
create_minimum --for busy_day --time 10min --include "2min breathwork, 3min intention, 5min movement"

# Evening Design
create_evening --sleep_target 11pm --start 9:30pm --include "9:30 dim lights, 9:45 phone away, 10:00 read, 10:30 breathwork, 10:45 lights out"
prepare_tomorrow --include "lay out clothes, pack bag, review calendar, write top 3 priorities"

# Optimization
audit_routine --current described --identify "checking phone first thing (friction), no transition between work and personal (missing)"
add_transition --between work_and_home --insert "10min walk, change clothes, 5min silent tea" --purpose "context switching"

# Review
monthly_review --routine current --ask "What's actually serving me? What's just habit? What am I avoiding that would help?"
evolve_routine --season summer --adjust earlier_wake sunlight_exposure lighter_exercise outdoor_elements

Pillar Mapping
Primary: 🧠 MIND
Sub-field: Habits & Discipline
Synergies: Habit Coach (behavior design), Sleep Optimizer (evening routine), Meditation Guide (morning mindfulness)
